@@bCollapsed Cairn Station@@N~
@@yThe Reach Warden station here has been collapsed for long enough that young saltbush has rooted in the debris, its pale stems threading through the broken Saltglass tablet frames.@@N The roof structure came down in a single event — the main ridge beam snapped and pulled the entire assembly inward — and the remains are compressed into a low mound rather than scattered widely. @@yTablet fragments are visible throughout the debris: inventory inspection records, transit seal registers, and what appears to be an overdue ration report addressed to a Warden post three stations back along the Reach.@@N A partial wall still stands to the north, preserving a half-legible Survey-Administrative inscription that once displayed the full transit procedure for arriving caravans. @@bThe collapsed station marks the western edge of what was once the Tidemouth Dune checkpoint zone, before the administrative boundary was moved to the Shoreward Seal.@@N
