#14216
@@yThe Shoreward Seal@@N~
@@yA basalt column stands at the centre of the approach corridor, twice the height of a person and polished smooth on its eastern face.@@N The column is inscribed on four sides in two different legal registers — the western face carries the Survey-Administrative notation of the Saltglass Reach authority, and the eastern face bears the Harbor-Operational Measure Script of Mafdet's Shoreward Compact. Together they define the legal threshold: west of this marker, inland charter law applies; east, maritime contract law governs all cargo obligations. @@yThe inscription on the western face reads: EASTERN LIMIT OF SALTGLASS REACH JURISDICTION — TRANSIT SEALS MUST BE CURRENT — CARAVAN MANIFESTS PRESENTED FOR SHOREWARD CONVERSION AT LANDWARD GATE.@@N @@lThe eastern face in Measure Script reads: SALTWEIGHT STANDARD ASSUMES JURISDICTION — ALL CARGO WEIGHTS RECALIBRATED TO HARBOR MEASURE FROM THIS POINT.@@N The ground around the base of the column has been worn smooth by the feet of travellers stopping to read it, and several small tokens — a bent coin, a cairn chalk stick, a fragment of coloured thread — have been left at its base. The column itself is in excellent repair, recently re-inscribed along the Survey-Administrative face, and has clearly been maintained with deliberate care.
